2.Explain difference between JPA and Hibernate:
‚óè Explain Layered Architecture:

Answer :- 

A : JPA
a. It is defined in javax.persistence package.

b. Java Persistence API (JPA) defines the management of relational data in the Java applications.

c. It uses Java Persistence Query Language (JPQL) as an object-oriented 
query language to perform database operations.

B : Hibernate

a. Hibernate is an Object-Relational Mapping (ORM) tool which is used to save the state of Java object into
 the database.
 
b. It is defined in org.hibernate package.

c. It uses Hibernate Query Language (HQL) as an object-oriented query language to
 perform database operations.

 
 
 Explain Layered Architecture:
 
 Anser :-The layered architecture style is one of the most common architectural styles. 
  The idea behind Layered Architecture is that modules or components with similar
  functionalities are organized into horizontal layers. 
  One of the benefit is our code will be easier to understand.
 
 